French Prime Minister Manuel Valls is to announce later on Monday that he will run for president in next year&#8217;s election, Agence France Presse and French television reported.Valls&#8217; office issued a statement that he would make a declaration at 1730 GMT, but it gave no further details.Valls&#8217; expected announcement follows a primary ballot in which Francois Fillon, a 62-year-old former prime minister, secured a resounding win to become the presidential candidate of the centre-right Les Republicains party.France&#8217;s presidential election takes place in two rounds next April and May.The ruling Socialists, now behind Les Republicains and the far-right National Front parties in opinion polls, are organising a primary in January to pick their candidate.-Reuters